race.comment: HARRY'S YACHT (1) gets the right scenario to return to the winner's stall. He found 1600m too far at Flemington but ran well over this route last time when getting too far back and covering ground, finding the line strongly for third despite that. Drawn the inside here can see him settle on the leader's back and that could prove the difference over STEALTH OF NIGHT (12) who beat him home last time. STEALTH OF NIGHT is drawn very wide but will roll forward regardless. If she gets across early she'll go close. PORTER (6) was fourth in the same race last time, unable to replicate his loose lead and big win at Flemington. He'll be thereabouts again. TWO WOLVES (13) has won two in a row and drops 4kg off last start. He can measure up strongly. BLACK STORM (2) is back in trip but can be staying on.
